In heritrix 3 I would start by adding this rule to your scope. It will 
reject urls that end with common image extensions (.png .jpg .gif etc)

&lt;bean class=&quot;org.archive.modules.deciderules.MatchesFilePatternDecideRule&quot;&gt;
&lt;property name=&quot;decision&quot; value=&quot;REJECT&quot;/&gt;
&lt;property name=&quot;usePreset&quot; value=&quot;IMAGES&quot; /&gt;
&lt;/bean&gt;

Not all images match the patterns hard-coded in that rule, so you could 
come up with a more elaborate regular expression that better matches 
what you find on the websites you&#39;re crawling. In some cases it may be 
impossible to know if a url is an image until it has been crawled, so 
you can also choose not to archive it, using a scope rule on the writer. 
But I would start simple with the MatchesFilePatternDecideRule.

Noah


